{"title_page": "Antonov An-188", "text_new": "{{Expand language|topic=|langcode=uk|otherarticle=\u0410\u043d-188|date=December 2019}}\n{{Cleanup|date=December 2019|reason=wording, page format}}\n{|{{Infobox aircraft begin\n  |name=An-188\n  |image=\n  |caption=\n}}{{Infobox aircraft type\n  |type =[[Military transport aircraft]]\n  |national origin = [[Ukraine]]\n  |design group = [[Antonov]]\n  |manufacturer = [[Antonov Serial Production Plant]]\n  |first flight = \n  |introduction =\n  |introduced      = <!--Date the aircraft entered or will enter military or revenue service -->\n  |retired =\n  |status = Development\n  |primary user    =\n  |more users      =\n  |produced        = <!--Years in production (e.g. 1970\u201399) if still in active use but no longer built -->\n  |number built    = <!-- Total number of flight-worthy aircraft completed. -->\n  |program cost = \n  |unit cost = \n  |developed from = [[Antonov An-70]]\n  |variants with their own articles = <!--Variants OF this aircraft-->\n  |developed into  = <!--For derivative aircraft based on this aircraft-->\n}}\n|}\n'''Antonov An-188'''&nbsp;\u2014 project of [[Ukraine|ukrainian]] a promising average multipurpose [[military transport aircraft]] with short takeoff and landing.\n\nIt was announced at the 51st International [[Paris Air Show]] - 2015. In essence, it is a modification of the [[Antonov An-70|An-70]] with four turbojet engines manufactured by JSC [[Motor Sich]] - D-436-148FM or the latest AI-28 instead of turbofan [[Progress D-27|D-27]]. Aircraft equipment and engines from other manufacturers are possible.\n\nAccording to the purpose, the aircraft occupies a niche between the average transport aircraft [[Lockheed Martin C-130J Super Hercules|C-130J-30]] and the heavy [[Boeing C-17 Globemaster III|C-17A]].\n\n[[Maximum takeoff weight]] \u2014 140 tons.\n\n[[Payload]] \u2014 40 tons.\n\nSpecifications will allow operation on soil [[runway]]s up to 915 m (3,000 feet) in length.\n\nFuel consumption is estimated at 4,600&nbsp;kg/h.\n\n== Videos ==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P2qUO_kh_DU&t=22s Model An-188 at Eurasia-2018 International Air Show]\n\n== Hoaxes ==\n* [[Airbus A400M Atlas]]\n* [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|Lockheed Martin C-130J]]\n* [[Boeing C-17 Globemaster III]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Cargo aircraft]]\n* {{ill|Antonov An-77|uk|\u0410\u043d-77}}\n\n== \u0414\u0436\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0430 ==\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.janes.com/article/52287/paris-air-show-2015-antonov-reveals-an-188-strategic-transport-aircraft |title=Paris Air Show 2015: Antonov reveals An-188 strategic transport aircraft |author=Nicholas de Larrinaga, London |date=16 June 2015 |website=www.janes.com |publisher= IHS Jane's Defence Weekly|accessdate=2015-07-22}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.ukrinform.ua/ukr/news/ukraiina_pokazala_le_burge_proekt_novogo_transportnika_2064763 |title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u041b\u0435 \u0411\u0443\u0440\u0436\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 |author= |date=2015-06-17 |website=www.ukrinform.ua |publisher=Ukrinform |accessdate=2015-07-18 }}\n*{{cite web |url=http://cacds.org.ua/ru/comments/356 |title=\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e \u041a\u0406\u0412\u0410: \"\u0414\u041f \"\u0410\u041d\u0422\u041e\u041d\u041e\u0412\". \u0412\u0456\u0439\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e-\u0442\u0435\u0445\u043d\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0435 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0456\u0442\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0432 \u0430\u0432\u0456\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0433\u0430\u043b\u0443\u0437\u0456\" |author= |date=2014-10-03 |website=cacds.org.ua |publisher=\u0426\u0414\u0410\u041a\u0420 |accessdate=2016-03-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425155349/http://cacds.org.ua/ru/comments/356 |archivedate=2016-04-25 |url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://mil.in.ua/an-178-stvoryuyetsya-spilne-ukrayino-turecke-pidpryyemstvo/ |title=\u0410\u043d-188: \u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044e\u0454\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435 \u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u043e-\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0435 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0438\u0454\u043c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e |author= |date=2018-07-17 |website=mil.in.ua |publisher=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0456\u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |accessdate=2018-07-17}}\n* {{cite web |url=http://uprom.info/news/avia/odna-z-versiy-novogo-transportnogo-litaka-an-188-otrimaye-dviguni-virobleni-u-ssha/ |title=\u041e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0437 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0456\u0439 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0430 \u0410\u043d-188 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0454 \u0434\u0432\u0438\u0433\u0443\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0456 \u0443 \u0421\u0428\u0410 |author= |date=2018-07-31 |website=uprom.info |publisher=\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |accessdate=2018-07-31}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://uprom.info/news/avia/ukrayina-ta-turechchyna-domovlyayutsya-pro-spilne-litakobuduvannya/ |title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0430 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0432\u043b\u044f\u044e\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435 \u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f |author= |date=2019-12-26 |website=uprom.info |publisher=\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl= |accessdate=2019-12-26}}\n\n{{Antonov aircraft}}\n\n[[Category:Antonov aircraft|An-188]]\n", "text_old": "{{Expand language|topic=|langcode=uk|otherarticle=\u0410\u043d-188|date=December 2019}}\n{{Cleanup|date=December 2019|reason=wording, page format}}\n{|{{Infobox aircraft begin\n  |name=An-188\n  |image=\n  |caption=\n}}{{Infobox aircraft type\n  |type =[[Military transport aircraft]]\n  |national origin = [[Ukraine]]\n  |design group = [[Antonov]]\n  |manufacturer = [[Antonov Serial Production Plant]]\n  |first flight = \n  |introduction =\n  |introduced      = <!--Date the aircraft entered or will enter military or revenue service -->\n  |retired =\n  |status = Development\n  |primary user    =\n  |more users      =\n  |produced        = <!--Years in production (e.g. 1970\u201399) if still in active use but no longer built -->\n  |number built    = <!-- Total number of flight-worthy aircraft completed. -->\n  |program cost = \n  |unit cost = \n  |developed from = [[Antonov An-70]]\n  |variants with their own articles = <!--Variants OF this aircraft-->\n  |developed into  = <!--For derivative aircraft based on this aircraft-->\n}}\n|}\n'''Antonov An-188'''&nbsp;\u2014 project of [[Ukraine|ukrainian]] a promising average multipurpose [[military transport aircraft]] with short takeoff and landing.\n\nIt was announced at the 51st International [[Paris Air Show]] - 2015. In essence, it is a modification of the [[Antonov An-70|An-70]] with four turbojet engines manufactured by JSC [[Motor Sich]] - D-436-148FM or the latest AI-28 instead of turbofan [[Progress D-27|D-27]]. Aircraft equipment and engines from other manufacturers are possible.\n\nAccording to the purpose, the aircraft occupies a niche between the average transport aircraft [[Lockheed Martin C-130J Super Hercules|C-130J-30]] and the heavy [[Boeing C-17 Globemaster III|C-17A]].\n\n[[Maximum takeoff weight]] \u2014 140 tons.\n\n[[Payload]] \u2014 40 tons.\n\nSpecifications will allow operation on soil [[runway]]s up to 915 m (3,000 feet) in length.\n\nFuel consumption is estimated at 4,600&nbsp;kg/h.\n\n== Videos ==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P2qUO_kh_DU&t=22s Model An-188 at Eurasia-2018 International Air Show]\n\n== \u041a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 ==\n* [[Airbus A400M Atlas]]\n* [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|Lockheed Martin C-130J]]\n* [[Boeing C-17 Globemaster III]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Cargo aircraft]]\n* {{ill|Antonov An-77|uk|\u0410\u043d-77}}\n\n== \u0414\u0436\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0430 ==\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.janes.com/article/52287/paris-air-show-2015-antonov-reveals-an-188-strategic-transport-aircraft |title=Paris Air Show 2015: Antonov reveals An-188 strategic transport aircraft |author=Nicholas de Larrinaga, London |date=16 June 2015 |website=www.janes.com |publisher= IHS Jane's Defence Weekly|accessdate=2015-07-22}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.ukrinform.ua/ukr/news/ukraiina_pokazala_le_burge_proekt_novogo_transportnika_2064763 |title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u041b\u0435 \u0411\u0443\u0440\u0436\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 |author= |date=2015-06-17 |website=www.ukrinform.ua |publisher=Ukrinform |accessdate=2015-07-18 }}\n*{{cite web |url=http://cacds.org.ua/ru/comments/356 |title=\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e \u041a\u0406\u0412\u0410: \"\u0414\u041f \"\u0410\u041d\u0422\u041e\u041d\u041e\u0412\". \u0412\u0456\u0439\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e-\u0442\u0435\u0445\u043d\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0435 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0456\u0442\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0432 \u0430\u0432\u0456\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0433\u0430\u043b\u0443\u0437\u0456\" |author= |date=2014-10-03 |website=cacds.org.ua |publisher=\u0426\u0414\u0410\u041a\u0420 |accessdate=2016-03-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425155349/http://cacds.org.ua/ru/comments/356 |archivedate=2016-04-25 |url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://mil.in.ua/an-178-stvoryuyetsya-spilne-ukrayino-turecke-pidpryyemstvo/ |title=\u0410\u043d-188: \u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044e\u0454\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435 \u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u043e-\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0435 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0438\u0454\u043c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e |author= |date=2018-07-17 |website=mil.in.ua |publisher=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0456\u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |accessdate=2018-07-17}}\n* {{cite web |url=http://uprom.info/news/avia/odna-z-versiy-novogo-transportnogo-litaka-an-188-otrimaye-dviguni-virobleni-u-ssha/ |title=\u041e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0437 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0456\u0439 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0430 \u0410\u043d-188 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0454 \u0434\u0432\u0438\u0433\u0443\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0456 \u0443 \u0421\u0428\u0410 |author= |date=2018-07-31 |website=uprom.info |publisher=\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |accessdate=2018-07-31}}\n* {{cite web |url=https://uprom.info/news/avia/ukrayina-ta-turechchyna-domovlyayutsya-pro-spilne-litakobuduvannya/ |title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0430 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0432\u043b\u044f\u044e\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435 \u043b\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f |author= |date=2019-12-26 |website=uprom.info |publisher=\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043b |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl= |accessdate=2019-12-26}}\n\n{{Antonov aircraft}}\n\n[[Category:Antonov aircraft|An-188]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7d:16a0:1b00:849a:c25f:539f:eafc", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200e\u041a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438/See Also)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonov_An-188"}
{"title_page": "Motets by Johann Sebastian Bach, discography", "text_new": "This article includes a list of commercial recordings of the [[Motet (Bach)|motets]] of [[Johann Sebastian Bach]]. Bach motets have often been recorded as a set (typically comprising the six motets catalogued as BWV{{nbsp}}225-230).{{efn|\"BWV\" is [[Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis]], a thematic catalogue of Bach's works.}}  However, other motets are attributed to Bach and there is some doubt about the authorship of [[Lobet den Herrn, alle Heiden, BWV 230|''Lobet den Herrn, alle Heiden'', BWV 230]], one of the {{abbr|BWV|Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis (catalogue of Bach's works)}} \"six\".\n\nA single CD can contain the set of six motets plus other works. For example, [[Maasaki Suzuki]]'s 2009 recording on [[BIS Records|BIS]] includes [[O Jesu Christ, meins Lebens Licht, BWV 118|''O Jesu Christ, meins Lebens Licht'', BWV 118]] (which at one time was categorised as a cantata) and [[Ich lasse dich nicht, BWV Anh. 159|''Ich lasse dich nicht'', BWV Anh. 159]] (the authorship of which has been disputed).<ref name=\"BIS\">{{Cite web |url=https://bis.se/conductors/suzuki-masaaki/bach-motets |title=Bach Motets |website=bis.se (BIS Records) |access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref> The motets chosen for a particular recording can reflect the way the balance of opinion changes regarding the status of a particular work. This appears to be the case with the two sets by [[John Eliot Gardiner]] conducting the [[Monteverdi Choir]]. They recorded Bach's motets without {{nowrap|BWV Anh. 159}} in 1980, but included it in their 2011 live recording.<ref name=\"muzie\">[https://www.muziekweb.nl/en/Link/DBX11558 ''Bach: Motets''] and [https://www.muziekweb.nl/en/Link/DBX10438 ''Bach Motets''] at {{url|www.muziekweb.nl}}.</ref>\n\n== Types of choirs ==\nChoirs with [[one voice per part]] (OVPP) are used in some [[historically informed performance]]s of Bach. However, OVPP recordings of the motets are relatively rare. Exceptions include the [[Hilliard Ensemble]]'s second set,<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{Cite news |last=Clements |first=Andrew |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2007/may/18/classicalmusicandopera.shopping2 |title=Bach: Motets |date=18 May 2007 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> and [[Konrad Jungh\u00e4nel]] with the group Cantus C\u00f6lln.<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas6\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec6.htm |title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 6 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n\nAt least some of the motets would have been first performed by singers from Leipzig's [[Thomanerchor]], which comprises boys and young men. This choir has recorded the motets (initially under [[G\u00fcnther Ramin]] in the 1950s),<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec2.htm  |title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 2 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref> as have other choirs with boys' voices such as the [[Choir of New College, Oxford]].<ref name=\"BachCantatas7\"/>\n\n== Instrumental accompaniment ==\nMusic directors need to make choices about the instrumental accompaniment, if any, to be used. One approach is to have instruments doubling the vocal lines, something which is described as playing ''[[colla parte]]''. The opposite approach is to be ''[[a cappella]]'', that is, without an accompaniment. It is also possible to have a compromise with some support for the singers from instruments such as an [[Organ (music)|organ]].\n\nSurviving sources do not make it clear what Bach's approach was to the accompaniment of most of these pieces. In the case of [[Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf, BWV 226|''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', BWV 226]] orchestral parts are extant, indicating that choir I was doubled by strings and choir II by reeds (two [[oboe]]s, [[Taille (instrument)|taille]] and [[bassoon]]). There is also a [[basso continuo]] (separate [[violone]] and organ parts are provided) which underlies both choirs.<ref name=\"bachchoir\">{{Cite web |url=https://bach.org/education/motet-bwv-226/ |title=Motet BWV 226 |website=Bach Choir of Bethlehem |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\nAn accompaniment is also specified for ''Lobet den Herrn''.<ref name=\"Leavis\">{{cite web | url= https://www.jstor.org/stable/731829| title=Bach's Setting of Psalm CXVII (BWV.230) | publisher=OUP | work=[[Music & Letters]]. Vol. 52, No. 1 | date=January 1971 | author=Leavis, Ralph}}  Accessed via JSTOR (subscription required)</ref>\n\nThe Hilliard Ensemble's OVPP version is mainly ''a capella''. They omit the instrumental parts of ''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', but sing ''Lobet den Herrn'' to organ accompaniment.<ref name=\"Guardian\"/>\n\n== History ==\nThe first of the motets to be recorded was [[Jesu, meine Freude, BWV 227|''Jesu meine Freude'']] in 1927. This version was sung in English.<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec1.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 1 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nIn 2010, Suzuki and his ensemble were given a French award ([[Diapason d'Or|Diapason d\u2019Or de l\u2019Ann\u00e9e]]) and a German award ([[Preis der deutschen Schallplattenkritik]]) for their recording of Bach motets on BIS.\n \nJohn Eliot Gardiner, who has won more [[Gramophone Classical Music Awards|Gramophone Awards]] than any other living artist, received one for his second recording of the motets with the Monteverdi Choir on SDG. It was one of the [[Gramophone_Classical_Music_Awards#2013|2013 awards]], the category being \"Baroque Vocal\".\n\nGrete Pedersen with the Norwegian choir [[Det Norske Solistkor]] won a Diapason d'Or in 2018 for their recording of the motets on BIS.\n\n== Discography ==\nThe intention has been to feature versions which are still available. The year given is that of recording. In the case of pre-1980s recordings, the date of reissue on CD can be significantly later than the original recording.\n{{Cantata discography header |work= Bach Motets |show_more=yes |more = Additional info}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Ramin\n| title = 6 Motetten<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas2\"/>\n| conductor = {{sortname|G\u00fcnther|Ramin}}\n| choir = [[Thomanerchor]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Archiv]] (reissue)\n| year = 1950s\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Christophers\n| title = The Six Motets<ref name=\"BachCantatas5\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec5.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 5 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|Harry|Christophers}}\n| choir = [[The Sixteen]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]]\n| year = 1989\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = \n| title = Bach Motetten\n| conductor = \n| choir = [[Hilliard Ensemble]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[ECM Records|ECM]]\n| year = 2003\n| more = second Hilliard recording\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Higginbottom\n| title = Bach Motets<ref name=\"BachCantatas7\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec7.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 7 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n| conductor = [[Edward Higginbottom]]\n| choir = [[Choir of New College, Oxford]]\n| instrumentalists = organ\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = Novum<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newcollegechoir.com/news/?pid=7&nid=1&storyid=12 |title=Recordings |website=Choir of New College, Oxford}}</ref>\n| year = 2008\n| more = organ accompaniment\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Suzuki\n| title = Bach Motets<ref name=\"BIS\"></ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|Masaaki|Suzuki}}\n| choir = [[Bach Collegium Japan]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[BIS Records|BIS]]\n| year = 2009\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Gardiner2\n| title =Bach Motets<ref name=\"muzie\"></ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|John Eliot|Gardiner}}\n| choir = [[Monteverdi Choir]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Soli Deo Gloria (record label)|SDG]]\n| year = 2011\n| more = second Gardiner recording\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Pedersen\n| title =\n| conductor = {{sortname|Grete|Pedersen}}\n| choir = [[Det Norske Solistkor|Norwegian Soloists' Choir]]\n| instrumentalists = Ensemble Allegria\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = BIS\n| year = 2017\n| more = \n}}\n{{End}}\n{{expand list|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of compositions by J. S. Bach]]\n", "text_old": "This article includes a list of commercial recordings of the [[Motet (Bach)|motets]] of [[Johann Sebastian Bach]]. Bach motets have often been recorded as a set (typically comprising the six motets catalogued as BWV{{nbsp}}225-230).{{efn|\"BWV\" is [[Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis]], a thematic catalogue of Bach's works.}}  However, other motets are attributed to Bach and there is some doubt about the authorship of [[Lobet den Herrn, alle Heiden, BWV 230|''Lobet den Herrn, alle Heiden'', BWV 230]], one of the {{abbr|BWV|Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis (catalogue of Bach's works)}} \"six\".\n\nA single CD can contain the set of six motets plus other works. For example, [[Maasaki Suzuki]]'s 2009 recording on [[BIS Records|BIS]] includes [[O Jesu Christ, meins Lebens Licht, BWV 118|''O Jesu Christ, meins Lebens Licht'', BWV 118]] (which at one time was categorised as a cantata) and [[Ich lasse dich nicht, BWV Anh. 159|''Ich lasse dich nicht'', BWV Anh. 159]] (the authorship of which has been disputed).<ref name=\"BIS\">{{Cite web |url=https://bis.se/conductors/suzuki-masaaki/bach-motets |title=Bach Motets |website=bis.se (BIS Records) |access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref> The motets chosen for a particular recording can reflect the way the balance of opinion changes regarding the status of a particular work. This appears to be the case with the two sets by [[John Eliot Gardiner]] conducting the [[Monteverdi Choir]]. They recorded Bach's motets without {{nowrap|BWV Anh. 159}} in 1980, but included it in their 2011 live recording.<ref name=\"muzie\">[https://www.muziekweb.nl/en/Link/DBX11558 ''Bach: Motets''] and [https://www.muziekweb.nl/en/Link/DBX10438 ''Bach Motets''] at {{url|www.muziekweb.nl}}.</ref>\n\n== Types of choirs ==\nChoirs with [[one voice per part]] (OVPP) are used in some [[historically informed performance]]s of Bach. However, OVPP recordings of the motets are relatively rare. Exceptions include the [[Hilliard Ensemble]]'s second set,<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{Cite news |last=Clements |first=Andrew |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2007/may/18/classicalmusicandopera.shopping2 |title=Bach: Motets |date=18 May 2007 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> and [[Konrad Jungh\u00e4nel]] with the group Cantus C\u00f6lln.<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas6\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec6.htm |title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 6 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n\nAt least some of the motets would have been first performed by singers from Leipzig's [[Thomanerchor]], which comprises boys and young men. This choir has recorded the motets (initially under [[G\u00fcnther Ramin]] in the 1950s),<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec2.htm  |title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 2 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref> as have other choirs with boys voices such as the [[Choir of New College, Oxford]].<ref name=\"BachCantatas7\"/>\n\n== Instrumental accompaniment ==\nMusic directors need to make choices about the instrumental accompaniment, if any, to be used. One approach is to have instruments doubling the vocal lines, something which is described as playing ''[[colla parte]]''. The opposite approach is to be ''[[a cappella]]'', that is, without an accompaniment. It is also possible to have a compromise with some support for the singers from instruments such as an [[Organ (music)|organ]].\n\nSurviving sources do not make it clear what Bach's approach was to the accompaniment of most of these pieces. In the case of [[Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf, BWV 226|''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', BWV 226]] orchestral parts are extant, indicating that choir I was doubled by strings and choir II by reeds (two [[oboe]]s, [[Taille (instrument)|taille]] and [[bassoon]]). There is also a [[basso continuo]] (separate [[violone]] and organ parts are provided) which underlies both choirs.<ref name=\"bachchoir\">{{Cite web |url=https://bach.org/education/motet-bwv-226/ |title=Motet BWV 226 |website=Bach Choir of Bethlehem |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\nAn accompaniment is also specified for ''Lobet den Herrn''.<ref name=\"Leavis\">{{cite web | url= https://www.jstor.org/stable/731829| title=Bach's Setting of Psalm CXVII (BWV.230) | publisher=OUP | work=[[Music & Letters]]. Vol. 52, No. 1 | date=January 1971 | author=Leavis, Ralph}}  Accessed via JSTOR (subscription required)</ref>\n\nThe Hilliard Ensemble's OVPP version is mainly ''a capella''. They omit the instrumental parts of ''Der Geist hilft unser Schwachheit auf'', but sing ''Lobet den Herrn'' to organ accompaniment.<ref name=\"Guardian\"/>\n\n== History ==\nThe first of the motets to be recorded was [[Jesu, meine Freude, BWV 227|''Jesu meine Freude'']] in 1927. This version was sung in English.<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec1.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 1 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\nIn 2010, Suzuki and his ensemble were given a French award ([[Diapason d'Or|Diapason d\u2019Or de l\u2019Ann\u00e9e]]) and a German award ([[Preis der deutschen Schallplattenkritik]]) for their recording of Bach motets on BIS.\n \nJohn Eliot Gardiner, who has won more [[Gramophone Classical Music Awards|Gramophone Awards]] than any other living artist, received one for his second recording of the motets with the Monteverdi Choir on SDG. It was one of the [[Gramophone_Classical_Music_Awards#2013|2013 awards]], the category being \"Baroque Vocal\".\n\nGrete Pedersen with the Norwegian choir [[Det Norske Solistkor]] won a Diapason d'Or in 2018 for their recording of the motets on BIS.\n\n== Discography ==\nThe intention has been to feature versions which are still available. The year given is that of recording. In the case of pre-1980s recordings, the date of reissue on CD can be significantly later than the original recording.\n{{Cantata discography header |work= Bach Motets |show_more=yes |more = Additional info}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Ramin\n| title = 6 Motetten<ref name=\"Bach Cantatas2\"/>\n| conductor = {{sortname|G\u00fcnther|Ramin}}\n| choir = [[Thomanerchor]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Archiv]] (reissue)\n| year = 1950s\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Christophers\n| title = The Six Motets<ref name=\"BachCantatas5\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec5.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 5 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|Harry|Christophers}}\n| choir = [[The Sixteen]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Hyperion Records|Hyperion]]\n| year = 1989\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = \n| title = Bach Motetten\n| conductor = \n| choir = [[Hilliard Ensemble]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[ECM Records|ECM]]\n| year = 2003\n| more = second Hilliard recording\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Higginbottom\n| title = Bach Motets<ref name=\"BachCantatas7\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Vocal/BWV225-231-Rec7.htm|title= Motets / Recordings \u2013 Part 7 |website=Bach Cantatas Website}}</ref>\n| conductor = [[Edward Higginbottom]]\n| choir = [[Choir of New College, Oxford]]\n| instrumentalists = organ\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = Novum<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newcollegechoir.com/news/?pid=7&nid=1&storyid=12 |title=Recordings |website=Choir of New College, Oxford}}</ref>\n| year = 2008\n| more = organ accompaniment\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Suzuki\n| title = Bach Motets<ref name=\"BIS\"></ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|Masaaki|Suzuki}}\n| choir = [[Bach Collegium Japan]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[BIS Records|BIS]]\n| year = 2009\n| more =\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Gardiner2\n| title =Bach Motets<ref name=\"muzie\"></ref>\n| conductor = {{sortname|John Eliot|Gardiner}}\n| choir = [[Monteverdi Choir]]\n| instrumentalists =\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = [[Soli Deo Gloria (record label)|SDG]]\n| year = 2011\n| more = second Gardiner recording\n}}\n{{Cantata discography row\n| id = Pedersen\n| title =\n| conductor = {{sortname|Grete|Pedersen}}\n| choir = [[Det Norske Solistkor|Norwegian Soloists' Choir]]\n| instrumentalists = Ensemble Allegria\n| soloists = {{plainlist|\n}}\n| label = BIS\n| year = 2017\n| more = \n}}\n{{End}}\n{{expand list|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of compositions by J. S. Bach]]\n", "name_user": "Thoughtfortheday", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTypes of choirs:punctuation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motets_by_Johann_Sebastian_Bach,_discography"}
{"title_page": "Wran ministry (1986)", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox government cabinet\n| cabinet_name            = Eighth Wran ministry\n| cabinet_number          = 78th\n| jurisdiction            = [[Government of New South Wales]]\n| flag                    = \n| flag_border             = true\n| incumbent               = \n<!-- Commented out: | image                   = File:Neville Wran.jpg -->\n| caption                 = [[Premier of New South Wales|Premier]] [[Neville Wran]]\n| date_formed             = {{start date|1986|02|06|df=y}}\n| date_dissolved          = {{end date|1986|07|04|df=y}}\n| government_head         = [[Neville Wran]]\n| government_head_history = \n| deputy_government_head  = [[Ron Mulock]]\n| state_head              = [[Queen Elizabeth II]] (represented by [[James Rowland (RAAF officer)|Sir James Rowland]])\n| members_number          = 20\n| former_members_number   = \n| total_number            = \n| political_party         = [[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]\n| legislature_status      = \n| opposition_cabinet      = \n| opposition_parties      = [[Liberal Party of Australia (New South Wales Division)|Liberal]] [[National Party of Australia \u2013 NSW|National]] [[Coalition (Australia)|coalition]]\n| opposition_leader       = [[Nick Greiner]]\n| election                = \n| last_election           = \n| legislature_term        = \n| budget                  = \n| advice_and_consent1     = \n| advice_and_consent2     = \n<!-- etc. -->\n| incoming_formation      = \n| outgoing_formation      = \n| previous                = [[Wran ministry (1984\u201386)|Seventh Wran ministry]]\n| successor               = [[Unsworth ministry]]\n}}\nThe '''Wran ministry (1986)''' or '''Eighth Wran ministry''' was the 78th ministry of the [[New South Wales Government]], and was led by the 35th [[Premier of New South Wales]], the Honourable [[Neville Wran]], {{post-nominals|AUS|QC|MP}}, representing the [[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor Party]]. It was the eighth of eight consecutive and final occasions when Wran was Premier.\n\n==Background==\n\n{{Empty section|date=May 2014}}\n\n==Tenure of ministry==\nThe ministry covers the period from 6 February 1986 when Wran reconfigured his ministry, until 4 July 1986 when Wran resigned from the ministry and from Parliament. [[Barrie Unsworth]] was elected by Labor caucus as the [[Leader of the Australian Labor Party in New South Wales|Labor Leader]], accepted commission as Premier and the [[Unsworth ministry]] was formed.\n\nMinisters are listed in order of seniority.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/key/Archives_MemberPage |title=Former Members - Chronological List of Ministries 1856 to 2009 (requires download) |work=Project for the Sesquicentenary of Responsible Government in NSW  |publisher=Parliament of New South Wales |format=[[Microsoft Excel|MS Excel spreadsheet]] |accessdate=26 April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Wah |first=Malvyne Jong |author2=Page, Jeffrey E. |date=November 2007 |title=New South Wales Parliamentary Record 1824 &ndash; 2007 |volume=VI |pages=[http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/cbe381f08171c2e8ca256fca007d6044/660e50b1b26c72acca257cc3007fd15b/$FILE/Part%206.pdf#page=52 52] |publisher=[[Parliament of New South Wales]] |url=http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/cbe381f08171c2e8ca256fca007d6044/660e50b1b26c72acca257cc3007fd15b/$FILE/Part%206.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=26 April 2014 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!colspan=1|Portfolio\n!colspan=1|Minister\n!colspan=\"2\" width=10%|Party\n!colspan=1|Term commence\n!colspan=1|Term end\n!colspan=1|Term of office\n|-\n|Premier<br>[[Minister for the Arts (New South Wales)|Minister for the Arts]]<br>Minister for Ethnic Affairs\n|Hon. [[Neville Wran]], {{post-nominals|AUS|QC|MP}}\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|rowspan=20 |[[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]\n|rowspan=20 align=\"center\"|6 February 1986\n|rowspan=20 align=\"center\"|4 July 1986\n|rowspan=20 align=\"center\"|{{age in days|1986|02|06|1986|07|04}} days\n|-\n|[[Deputy Premier of New South Wales|Deputy Premier]]<br>[[Minister for Transport (New South Wales)|Minister for Transport]]\n|Hon. [[Ron Mulock]], MP\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|Minister for Housing\n|Hon. [[Frank Walker (Australian politician)|Frank Walker]], {{post-nominals|AUS|QC|MP}}\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[NSW Public Works|Minister for Public Works]] and [[Minister for Transport (New South Wales)#Ministers for Ports and Waterways|Ports]]<br>[[Minister for Transport (New South Wales)#Ministers for Roads|Minister for Roads]]\n|Hon. [[Laurie Brereton]], MP \n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Minister for Industrial Relations (New South Wales)|Minister for Industrial Relations]]\n|Hon. [[Pat Hills]], MP\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|Minister for Youth and Community Services<br>[[Minister for Aboriginal Affairs (New South Wales)|Minister for Aboriginal Affairs]]<br>Minister Assisting the Premier\n|Hon. [[Peter Anderson (politician)|Peter Anderson]], MP \n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Treasurer of New South Wales|Treasurer]]\n|Hon. [[Ken Booth (politician)|Ken Booth]], MP\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Attorney General of New South Wales|Attorney General]]<br>Minister for Co-operative Societies\n|Hon. [[Terry Sheahan]], MP\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Minister for Health (New South Wales)|Minister for Health]]<br>Vice-President of the Executive Council<br>Leader of the Government in Legislative Council\n|Hon. [[Barrie Unsworth]], MLC\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Minister for Primary Industries (New South Wales)|Minister for Agriculture and Fisheries]]\n|Hon. [[Jack 