ox | before=[[Wran ministry (1984\u20131986)]] | title=Eighth Wran ministry | years=1986 | after=[[Unsworth ministry]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Ministries of New South Wales}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wran ministry (1986)}}\n[[Category:New South Wales ministries]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:1986 disestablishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Australian Labor Party ministries in New South Wales]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox government cabinet\n| cabinet_name            = Eighth Wran ministry\n| cabinet_number          = 78th\n| jurisdiction            = [[Government of New South Wales]]\n| flag                    = \n| flag_border             = true\n| incumbent               = \n<!-- Commented out: | image                   = File:Neville Wran.jpg -->\n| caption                 = [[Premier of New South Wales|Premier]] [[Neville Wran]]\n| date_formed             = {{start date|1986|02|06|df=y}}\n| date_dissolved          = {{end date|1986|07|04|df=y}}\n| government_head         = [[Neville Wran]]\n| government_head_history = \n| deputy_government_head  = [[Ron Mulock]]\n| state_head              = [[Queen Elizabeth II]] (represented by [[James Rowland (RAAF officer)|Sir James Rowland]])\n| members_number          = 20\n| former_members_number   = \n| total_number            = \n| political_party         = [[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor]]\n| legislature_status      = \n| opposition_cabinet      = \n| opposition_parties      = [[Liberal Party of Australia (New South Wales Division)|Liberal]] [[National Party of Australia \u2013 NSW|National]] [[Coalition (Australia)|coalition]]\n| opposition_leader       = [[Nick Greiner]]\n| election                = \n| last_election           = \n| legislature_term        = \n| budget                  = \n| advice_and_consent1     = \n| advice_and_consent2     = \n<!-- etc. -->\n| incoming_formation      = \n| outgoing_formation      = \n| previous                = [[Wran ministry (1984\u201386)|Seventh Wran ministry]]\n| successor               = [[Unsworth ministry]]\n}}\nThe '''Wran ministry (1986)''' or '''Eighth Wran ministry''' was the 78th ministry of the [[New South Wales Government]], and was led by the 35th [[Premier of New South Wales]], the Honourable [[Neville Wran]], {{post-nominals|AUS|QC|MP}}, representing the [[Australian Labor Party (New South Wales Branch)|Labor Party]]. It was the eighth of eight consecutive and final occasions when Wran was Premier.\n\n==Background==\n\n{{Empty section|date=May 2014}}\n\n==Tenure of ministry==\nThe ministry covers the period from 6 February 1986 when Wran reconfigured his ministry, until 4 July 1986 when Wran resigned from the ministry and from Parliament. [[Barrie Unsworth]] was elected by Labor caucus as the [[Leader of the Australian Labor Party in New South Wales|Labor Leader]], accepted commission as Premier and the [[Unsworth ministry]] was formed.\n\nMinisters are listed in order of seniority.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/key/Archives_MemberPage |title=Former Members - Chronological List of Ministries 1856 to 2009 (requires download) |work=Project for the Sesquicentenary of Responsible Government in NSW  |publisher=Parliament of New South Wales |format=[[Microsoft Excel|MS Excel spreadsheet]] |accessdate=26 April 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Wah |first=Malvyne Jong |author2=Page, Jeffrey E. |date=November 2007 |title=New South Wales Parliamentary Record 1824 &ndash; 2007 |volume=VI |pages=[http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/cbe381f08171c2e8ca256fca007d6044/660e50b1b26c72acca257cc3007fd15b/$FILE/Part%206.pdf#page=52 52] |publisher=[[Parliament of New South Wales]] |url=http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/web/common.nsf/cbe381f08171c2e8ca256fca007d6044/660e50b1b26c72acca257cc3007fd15b/$FILE/Part%206.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=26 April 2014 }}</ref